    "type": "heading",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "15.1.1 GAN loss function"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b002",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 2,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "We now define the loss function for training GANs more precisely. The discriminator $f[x, \\phi]$ takes input x, has parameters $\\phi$ , and returns a scalar that is higher when it believes the input is a real example. This is a binary classification task, so w"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b003",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 3,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "\\begin{aligned}\n\\hat{\\phi}\n&=\\underset{\\phi}{\\mathrm{argmin}}\\left[\n\\sum_{i}-(1-y_{i})\\log\\left[1-\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x}_{i},\\phi]]\\right]\n-y_{i}\\log\\left[\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x}_{i},\\phi]]\\right]\n\\right],\n\\end{aligned}\n\\tag{15.2}"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b004",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 4,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "where $y_{i} \\in \\lbrace 0,1 \\rbrace$ is the label, and $\\mathrm{sig}[\\bullet]$ is the logistic sigmoid function (figure 5.7)."
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b005",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 5,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "In this case, we assume that the real examples x have label y = 1 and the generated samples $x^{*}$ have label y = 0 so that:"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b006",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 6,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "\\begin{aligned}\n\\hat{\\phi}\n&=\\underset{\\phi}{\\mathrm{argmin}}\\left[\n\\sum_{j}-\\log\\left[1-\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x}_{j}^{*},\\phi]]\\right]\n-\\sum_{i}\\log\\left[\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x}_{i},\\phi]]\\right]\n\\right],\n\\end{aligned}\n\\tag{15.3}"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b007",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 7,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "where i and j index the real examples and generated samples, respectively."
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b008",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 8,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "Now we substitute the definition for the generator $x_{j}^{*} = \\mathrm{g}[z_{j}, \\theta]$ and note that we must maximize with respect to $\\theta$ since we want the generated samples to be misclassified (i.e., have low likelihood of being synthetic or high negative log-likelihood):"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b009",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 9,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "\\begin{aligned}\n\\hat{\\theta}\n&=\\underset{\\theta}{\\mathrm{argmax}}\\left[\n\\min_{\\phi}\\left[\n\\sum_{j}-\\log\\left[1-\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathrm{g}[z_{j},\\theta],\\phi]]\\right]\n-\\sum_{i}\\log\\left[\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x}_{i},\\phi]]\\right]\n\\right]\\right].\n\\end{aligned}\n\\tag{15.4}"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b010",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 10,
    "type": "heading",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "15.1.2 Training GANs"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b011",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 11,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "Equation 15.4 is a more complex loss function than we have seen before; the discriminator parameters $\\phi$ are manipulated to minimize the loss function, and the generative parameters $\\theta$ are manipulated to maximize the loss function. GAN training is cha"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b012",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 12,
    "type": "paragraph",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "To train the GAN, we can divide equation 15.4 into two loss functions:"
  },
  {
    "id": "page_0278-b013",
    "page_key": 278,
    "order": 13,
    "type": "equation",
    "source": "deepseek+paddle",
    "confidence": "high",
    "text": "\\begin{aligned}\nL[\\phi]&=\\sum_{j}-\\log\\left[1-\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathrm{g}[z_{j},\\theta],\\phi]]\\right]-\\sum_{i}\\log\\left[\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathbf{x}_{i},\\phi]]\\right]\\\\\nL[\\theta]&=\\sum_{j}\\log\\left[1-\\mathrm{sig}[f[\\mathrm{g}[z_{j},\\theta],\\phi]]\\right],\n\\end{aligned}\n\\tag{15.5}"
  }
]
